response.body:
{ "letterHtml": "

This is to inform you pursuant to New Orleans City Code Section 2-1121 (the Police Monitors Ordinance) that the Office of the Independent Police Monitor (OIPM) has received a complaint of misconduct by an NOPD employee(s). The complainant relayed the following information to our office:



Complaint Information


Date filed with OIPM: 07/21/2020


Complainant InformationSusie and Phoebe and Sarah are the G.O.A.T.s

Name: Night Watch

Race: Black, African American

Sex: Other

Phone: (123) 456-7890


Subject NOPD Employee(s) Information

Name: Ansel W Rice

Rank: POLICE OFFICER 1

Employee ID: #9550

Race: White

Sex: M

Employee Type: Commissioned

Bureau: FOB - Field Operations Bureau

Status: Terminated

End of Employment: 12/28/2003


Witnesses

Name: Amira E Jaskolski

Rank: POLICE LIEUTENANT

Employee ID: #7994

Race: Black / African American

Sex: M

Supervisor (Employee ID): Everardo R Wiegand (#11819)

Employee Type: Commissioned

District: 7th District

Bureau: FOB - Field Operations Bureau

Status: Active


Incident

Date: 12/20/2017

Location: Bourbon St & Canal St, New Orleans, LA 70112

Time: 02:31 AM CST



Initial Allegations/Concerns/Issues


Complainant alleges the following occurred on 12/20/2017, during the complainants interaction with POLICE OFFICER 1 Ansel W Rice. If proven, the accused may have violated NOPD policy, rules, or procedure when:

  1. Used department property. This is in violation of Rule 7: Departmental Property: PARAGRAPH 01 - Use of Department Property


Details of Complainants Account


test details data



Complaint History


The OIPM has reviewed POLICE OFFICER 1 Ansel W Rice's disciplinary history for the last five years and has determined that the subject employee has the following significant/noteworthy number of complaints:

  • 10 total complaints including 2 HIGH RISK allegations, 3 MEDIUM RISK allegations, 5 LOW RISK allegations.


Request for Review and Intervention


In light of the seriousness of the allegations and/or POLICE OFFICER 1 Ansel W Rice's complaint history, the OIPM requests that, pending the completion of this investigation, PIB review this officers history to ascertain if the accused officer should:

  • Be temporarily or permanently reassigned from his/her current assignment


Retaliation Concerns and Request for Notice to Accused


Based on the information provided by the complainant, the OIPM is concerned about retaliation against the complainant. We request that once the accused is made aware of this complaint that they be admonished in writing by their commanding officer(s) about retaliating against the Complainant, or from having others do so.



IAPro Corrections

  • IAPro Correction Details


Classification Recommendation
